  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The old club file had a faded photograph clipped to the front page, showing a small group of students by the school gate.",
      "zh": "那份舊社團資料的第一頁夾著一張褪色的照片，拍的是一小群學生站在校門口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The next morning, Coco asked Mr. Pan directly. \"Who started the Friday Box? Was it your idea?\"",
      "zh": "隔天早上，Coco 直接問潘老師：「Friday Box 是誰開始的？是你的主意嗎？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan looked up from his desk, and for a second, said nothing at all.",
      "zh": "潘老師從桌子那邊抬起頭來，有那麼一秒鐘，什麼都沒說。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's not really what the show is about,\" he said finally.",
      "zh": "他最後說：「這其實不是節目該談的東西。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice looked at him closely.",
      "zh": "Bernice 仔細地看著他。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's the first question you've ever tried not to answer,\" she said.",
      "zh": "她說：「這是你第一次不想回答的問題。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan almost smiled. \"You two really have gotten good at this.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師幾乎笑了：「你們兩個真的越來越擅長這個了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"So there is an answer,\" Coco said. \"You're just not ready to give it.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「所以是有答案的，你只是還沒準備好說出來。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan didn't argue with that.",
      "zh": "潘老師沒有反駁這句話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Instead of pushing further, they decided to try their usual first step: check the records.",
      "zh": "他們沒有繼續逼問，而是決定用平常的第一步：查資料。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The school office had a thin file about the podcast club, started six years ago.",
      "zh": "學校辦公室有一份關於這個 podcast 社團的薄薄資料，六年前成立的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan's name was listed as the teacher who asked for it, along with one short line: \"Reason: personal.\"",
      "zh": "資料上寫著潘老師是申請成立的老師，還有一行簡短的字：「原因：個人因素。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Personal,\" Bernice repeated. \"That's not much to work with.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 重複著：「個人因素，這句話不太夠用。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco kept reading. Under the club's original name, someone had written something different from \"The Friday Box.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 繼續讀下去。在社團原本的名字底下，有人寫了一個跟「Friday Box」不一樣的名字。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It said: \"The Ten Minute Club.\"",
      "zh": "上面寫著：「十分鐘社。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco went completely still for a second.",
      "zh": "Coco 有那麼一秒鐘完全靜止不動。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Ten minutes,\" she said slowly. \"Like the clock. Like case one.\"",
      "zh": "她慢慢地說：「十分鐘，就像那個鐘，就像案件一。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice's eyes went wide. \"Mr. Pan knew about Ms. Ho's clock before we ever found it, didn't he?\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 的眼睛睜大了：「潘老師在我們發現之前，就已經知道何老師的鐘了，對不對？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Neither of them said anything else for a long moment. Some questions, they were learning, needed time before you asked them out loud.",
      "zh": "有好長一段時間，他們兩個都沒再說話。他們漸漸明白，有些問題在說出口之前，需要一點時間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The old file also listed a small item nobody understood at first: a single glass jar, kept safe on a shelf in the office.",
      "zh": "那份舊資料裡還列了一件一開始沒人看懂的物品：一個被小心放在辦公室架上的玻璃罐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "In science class that week, they studied the earth, the moon, and how each planet moved around the sun.",
      "zh": "那個星期的科學課，他們學習地球、月亮，還有每顆行星怎麼繞著太陽轉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One night, Mr. Pan brought a small telescope so anyone could look at a bright star after class.",
      "zh": "有天晚上，潘老師帶了一台小望遠鏡，讓下課後想看星星的人都可以看。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Nature doesn't care about our school schedule,\" he said, looking up at the clear, cold sky.",
      "zh": "他抬頭看著清澈寒冷的夜空說：「大自然才不管我們學校的課表。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice joked that even a small rock on the ground had probably existed longer than their entire school building.",
      "zh": "Bernice 開玩笑說，地上一顆小石頭大概都比他們整棟學校還要古老。"
    }
  ],
